Criminal Record Management System

The Criminal Record Management System (CRMS) is a web-based application designed to efficiently manage and maintain criminal records for law enforcement agencies or legal institutions. Developed using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js), this system offers a comprehensive solution for tracking, storing, and accessing information about individuals with criminal records.
Features:
User Authentication and Role Management:
Secure login for admins, law enforcement officers, and authorized personnel.
Role-based access control to ensure data privacy and security.

Criminal Profile Management:
Ability to create, read, update, and delete records.
Storage of detailed information such as name, photo, fingerprints, aliases, crime history, and convictions.

Case Management:
Record details of criminal cases, including case numbers, investigation status, court verdicts, and sentencing.

Search and Filter:
Advanced search functionality to find records based on various parameters like name, case number, or location.

Reports and Analytics:
Generate detailed reports on crime trends, location-based statistics, and case outcomes.
